{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Naively, this would seem to require at least O(m 2) depth, as there are m rotations, and deciding which qubit to inject for each requires O(m) rounds of controlled-swapping.",
    "[20] observed that this can be reduced to O(m) depth, assuming access to FANOUT-CNOT with O(M) targets that act in unit time.",
    "To decompose such a FANOUT-CNOT gate into two-qubit gates, at least O(m) depth would typically be required; thus, the depth of the Clader et al. [20] SPF implementation in the {U (2), CNOT} gate set would be O(m 2), not O(m).We give a circuit compilation method for reducing the depth back to O(m) using a few extra ancillae.",
    "We do so by interspersing the CSWAPs with copying layers.",
    "In particular, for each u = s + 1, s + 2,..., m -1, data qubit s is needed to control 2 u-1-s CSWAPs on the angle register that starts in state |Θ u ⟩."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
